casebody.data:
DISCIPLINARY DOCKET

94-2254. Cincinnati Bar Assn. v. Sullivan.

On November 9, 1995, this court ordered respondent, Sharon Sullivan, to show cause why she should not be found in contempt for failure to comply with this court’s April 5,1995 order. On November 29,1995, respondent filed a motion for hearing. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, effective February 12, 1996, that respondent’s motion be, and is hereby, granted, and that a hearing before the court be held on March 5,1996.

Douglas, Resnick and Cook, JJ., dissent.
